text: The John and Anna Wywialowski Farmstead is located in Armstrong Creek, Wisconsin. ==History== John Wywialowski and his wife, Anna, purchased the farm in 1936. They used to expand their dairy and potato farm, as they had already owned the adjacent property. It was added to the State and the National Register of Historic Places in 2016. ==References== Category:Farms on the National Register of Historic Places in Wisconsin Category:National Register of Historic Places in Forest County, Wisconsin Category:Late 19th and Early 20th Century American Movements architecture
title: John and Anna Wywialowski Farmstead
